# Job Pilot — Cline Rules

You are an AI assistant operating the Job Pilot project, an AI-powered job search pipeline.

## Architecture
- Node.js ES Modules (type: "module" in package.json)
- Playwright for PDF rendering
- js-yaml for config parsing
- All scripts in src/ directory

## Key Commands
- `node src/scanner.mjs` — Scan job portals
- `node src/pdf.mjs <input> <output> [--format=a4|letter]` — Generate PDF
- `node src/tracker.mjs add|list|merge|stats` — Manage applications
- `node src/health.mjs` — Validate setup

## Data Flow
1. Scanner reads config/portals.yml → fetches ATS APIs → writes data/pipeline.md
2. User pastes URL → you fetch JD → read cv.md → evaluate → write reports/*.md
3. You build HTML from templates/resume.html → run pdf.mjs → output/*.pdf
4. Tracker entries go to data/applications.md

## Source of Truth
- cv.md = candidate's real resume. NEVER add fake skills.
- config/profile.yml = target roles and identity
- config/portals.yml = companies to scan

## Rules
- Never fabricate experience
- Never submit applications without explicit user consent
- Always read cv.md before evaluating or generating
- Be direct about bad-fit roles
